column2: The School of Business and Social Sciences at the Aarhus University in Aarhus, Denmark, is affiliated with the European University Association, whose headquarters can be found in Brussels. Denmark's leader, Lars Lokke Rasmussen, is known as the Monarchy of Denmark and the Aarhus government has a magistrate.

column2: The School of Business and Social Sciences at the Aarhus University is located in Aarhus, Denmark and it was established in 1928. Its dean is Thomas Pallesen and it has 16,000 students. Its Latin name is Universitas Aarhusiensis. It is affiliated to the European University Association.
